Date: Mon, 08 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: Fix NanoPi NEO LED GPIO conflicts

Resolve two GPIO conflicts in the board-level LED nodes:

1. pwr (red) was on PL10, same as led-1 (green power) in
   sun8i-h3-nanopi.dtsi → move to PA0
2. status (green heartbeat) was on PA10, same as led-0
   (blue heartbeat) in sun8i-h3-nanopi.dtsi → move to PA1

Without these fixes, the gpio-leds driver fails to probe
with -EBUSY, leaving all LEDs unmanaged by the kernel.

--- a/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3-nanopi-neo.dts
+++ b/arch/arm/boot/dts/allwinner/sun8i-h3-nanopi-neo.dts
@@ -63,14 +63,14 @@

 		pwr {
 			label = "nanopi:red:pwr";
-			gpios = <&r_pio 0 10 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* PL10 */
+			gpios = <&pio 0 0 GPIO_ACTIVE_LOW>; /* PA0 */
 			linux,default-trigger = "default-on";
 		};

 		status {
 			label = "nanopi:green:status";
-			gpios = <&pio 0 10 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* PA10 */
+			gpios = <&pio 0 1 GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>; /* PA1 */
 			linux,default-trigger = "heartbeat";
 		};
 	};